The Vice President of the United States, Mike Pence, congratulated the 2017 Class of America's Astronauts during a speech at the Lyndon B. Johnson Space Center in Houston, Texas. Pence expressed his pride and the support of President Donald Trump for NASA's mission of exploration and discovery. He announced that President Trump will relaunch the National Space Council to ensure a coherent and cohesive approach to space exploration and technology. Pence emphasized the importance of deep space exploration and maintaining a constant presence in low-Earth orbit. He also praised the dedication and contributions of the thousands of men and women at NASA and its contractors. Pence concluded by addressing the 12 newly minted astronauts, urging them to embrace their role as heroes and trailblazers, and assuring them of the support and prayers of the American people.